description: This is a representation of figure 2 from T. Hla, et al. 2001, Science, 294, pg. 1877.  Sphingosine-1-phosphate (S1P) is a signaling sphingolipid, also known as lysosphingolipid. It is also referred to as a bioactive lipid mediator. Sphingolipids at large form a class of lipids characterized by a particular aliphatic aminoalcohol, which is sphingosine.
title: Signal transduction of S1P receptor
